2025-09-12 13:45:18 [INFO] Can continue: Ysgawyn
2025-09-12 13:45:18 [INFO] Can continue: If we were truly tied to Seren, we'd have all dropped<br>dead when she was shattered! The curse clearly doesn't<br>exist!
2025-09-12 13:45:18 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:19 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:19 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:45:19 [INFO] Can continue: Well... Don't be so sure of that.
2025-09-12 13:45:19 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:20 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:20 [INFO] Can continue: Ysgawyn
2025-09-12 13:45:20 [INFO] Can continue: Nice of you to suddenly speak up! I'd have thought a<br>king would command a bit of authority rather than<br>crying in the corner!
2025-09-12 13:45:20 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:21 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:21 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:45:21 [INFO] Can continue: I'm not a king any more...
2025-09-12 13:45:21 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:22 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:22 [INFO] Can continue: Ysgawyn
2025-09-12 13:45:22 [INFO] Can continue: Well thank Seren for that! You only managed to lose<br>the entire kingdom to Lord Iorwerth!
2025-09-12 13:45:22 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:23 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:23 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 13:45:23 [INFO] Can continue: You should learn some respect!
2025-09-12 13:45:23 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:24 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:24 [INFO] Can continue: Ysgawyn
2025-09-12 13:45:24 [INFO] Can continue: I have respect! I respect the heroes who died in this<br>war, not the coward that ran away from it!
2025-09-12 13:45:24 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:25 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:25 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:45:25 [INFO] Can continue: You... You're right. I failed you, I failed you all. I wish<br>I could go back and change that, but I can't. All I can<br>do now, is try and make things right.
2025-09-12 13:45:25 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:26 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:26 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:45:26 [INFO] Can continue: While horrifying, I believe PLAYER_NAME speaks the truth.<br>They have no reason to lie to us, and what they say<br>does make sense.
2025-09-12 13:45:26 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:27 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:27 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 13:45:27 [INFO] Can continue: How?
2025-09-12 13:45:27 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:29 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:29 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:45:29 [INFO] Can continue: Most of you never met Seren. You only know her<br>through the stories passed down to you. But I did know<br>her, and I know she was filled with pain.
2025-09-12 13:45:29 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:29 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:29 [INFO] Can continue: Ilfeen
2025-09-12 13:45:29 [INFO] Can continue: You... You think this is the reason?
2025-09-12 13:45:29 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:30 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:30 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:45:30 [INFO] Can continue: I think it could be. As for why we don't feel the effects<br>of the curse now, that is because Seren is still with us,<br>every one of us.
2025-09-12 13:45:30 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:31 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:31 [INFO] Can continue: Eluned
2025-09-12 13:45:31 [INFO] Can continue: Of course, the crystal seeds. All of us carry them in<br>some form or other, and all of them came from Seren<br>when she shattered herself.
2025-09-12 13:45:31 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:32 [INFO] LAG DETECTED 862ms
2025-09-12 13:45:32 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:32 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:45:32 [INFO] Can continue: Her last attempt to break the curse, after everything<br>else failed...
2025-09-12 13:45:32 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:33 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:33 [INFO] Can continue: Ilfeen
2025-09-12 13:45:33 [INFO] Can continue: So what do we do?
2025-09-12 13:45:33 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:34 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:34 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 13:45:34 [INFO] Can continue: There's one other thing. Seren built a second set of<br>defences within the Temple of Light, this fragment of<br>her is sealed within them. There's an orb that can<br>bypass these defences.
2025-09-12 13:45:34 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:36 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:36 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 13:45:36 [INFO] Can continue: An orb?
2025-09-12 13:45:36 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:37 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:37 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 13:45:37 [INFO] Can continue: Yes, apparently she hid it somewhere called Gorlah.
2025-09-12 13:45:37 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:38 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:38 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:45:38 [INFO] Can continue: I know of Gorlah. It's an old shrine north of Prifddinas,<br>a place for quiet worship away from the city.
2025-09-12 13:45:38 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:39 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:39 [INFO] Can continue: Ilfeen
2025-09-12 13:45:39 [INFO] Can continue: Does Lord Iorwerth know about the orb?
2025-09-12 13:45:39 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:40 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:40 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 13:45:40 [INFO] Can continue: Yes.
2025-09-12 13:45:40 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:42 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:42 [INFO] LAG DETECTED 757ms
2025-09-12 13:45:42 [INFO] Can continue: Eluned
2025-09-12 13:45:42 [INFO] Can continue: Then he might already have claimed it. We should send<br>someone to check.
2025-09-12 13:45:42 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:43 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:43 [INFO] Can continue: Ysgawyn
2025-09-12 13:45:43 [INFO] Can continue: I will go. I wish to see some actual proof of what this<br>human claims.
2025-09-12 13:45:43 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:44 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:44 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 13:45:44 [INFO] Can continue: That's not your call. Arianwyn is in charge here.
2025-09-12 13:45:44 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:45 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:45 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 13:45:45 [INFO] Can continue: Am I? My whole life, I've been fighting Lord Iorwerth.<br>My whole life, I've believed him to be a servant of<br>Zamorak. Now I learn that everything I fought for was<br>a lie.
2025-09-12 13:45:45 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:46 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:46 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 13:45:46 [INFO] Can continue: I don't even know what I'm leading any more...
2025-09-12 13:45:46 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:47 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:47 [INFO] Can continue: Ilfeen
2025-09-12 13:45:47 [INFO] Can continue: Maybe Lord Iorwerth fights for a different cause to<br>what we thought, but that doesn't change who he is, that<br>doesn't change what he's done.
2025-09-12 13:45:47 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:47 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:47 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 13:45:47 [INFO] Can continue: I need time alone... Time to think... Baxtorian, I would<br>appreciate it if you could take charge for a while.
2025-09-12 13:45:47 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:49 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:49 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:45:49 [INFO] Can continue: Oh... I... I'll do my best.
2025-09-12 13:45:49 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:49 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:49 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn
2025-09-12 13:45:49 [INFO] Can continue: That's all I ask. Now, I would like to be alone.
2025-09-12 13:45:49 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:51 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:51 [INFO] Can continue: Eluned
2025-09-12 13:45:51 [INFO] Can continue: You're not the only one. I think we all need time to<br>process this.
2025-09-12 13:45:51 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:52 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:52 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:45:52 [INFO] Can continue: Then let us close this meeting. We will reconvene later.
2025-09-12 13:45:52 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:53 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:55 [INFO] Can continue: The others leave the meeting.
2025-09-12 13:45:55 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:56 [INFO] DONE
2025-09-12 13:45:56 [INFO] Waiting for dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:58 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:58 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 13:45:58 [INFO] Can continue: So what do we do now?
2025-09-12 13:45:58 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:45:59 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:45:59 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:45:59 [INFO] Can continue: There's a lot to think about, for all of us. There's also a<br>lot we still don't know.
2025-09-12 13:45:59 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:46:00 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:46:00 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 13:46:00 [INFO] Can continue: Do you think Arianwyn will be okay?
2025-09-12 13:46:00 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:46:01 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:46:01 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:46:01 [INFO] Can continue: I hope so... I know the pain he feels, it can tear you<br>apart if you're not careful.
2025-09-12 13:46:01 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:46:03 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:46:03 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 13:46:03 [INFO] Can continue: You seem to be dealing with it okay.
2025-09-12 13:46:03 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:46:04 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:46:04 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:46:04 [INFO] Can continue: I'm glad it seems that way, that's not how it feels<br>though. I knew of Seren's troubles, but to know the<br>cause... it's heart-breaking.
2025-09-12 13:46:04 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:46:05 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:46:05 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:46:05 [INFO] Can continue: Now I find myself leading once more, something I<br>swore I would never do again.
2025-09-12 13:46:05 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:46:06 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:46:06 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 13:46:06 [INFO] Can continue: Arianwyn seems to think you're capable.
2025-09-12 13:46:06 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:46:07 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:46:07 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:46:07 [INFO] Can continue: Yes... But Arianwyn doesn't know me, not really.
2025-09-12 13:46:07 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:46:08 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:46:08 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:46:08 [INFO] Can continue: Anyway, I suppose my job now is to make sure we<br>don't lose sight of our goal.
2025-09-12 13:46:08 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:46:09 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:46:09 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 13:46:09 [INFO] Can continue: Do we know what that is anymore?
2025-09-12 13:46:09 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:46:10 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:46:10 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:46:10 [INFO] Can continue: To stop Lord Iorwerth. Even if we now know his true<br>intentions, even if some think those intentions may be<br>good, we can't ignore his actions.
2025-09-12 13:46:10 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:46:12 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:46:12 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:46:12 [INFO] Can continue: He'd see us all dead just to free this fragment of<br>Seren. He has to be stopped.
2025-09-12 13:46:12 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:46:12 [INFO] LAG DETECTED 849ms
2025-09-12 13:46:13 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:46:13 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 13:46:13 [INFO] Can continue: What do you need me to do?
2025-09-12 13:46:13 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:46:14 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:46:14 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:46:14 [INFO] Can continue: Ysgawyn has gone to see if he can find the orb you<br>spoke of. No one actually gave him permission, but he<br>seems to care little for orders at the moment.
2025-09-12 13:46:14 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 13:46:15 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 13:46:15 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 13:46:15 [INFO] Can continue: Once he gets back we'll know more about what to do<br>next. In the meantime, I've managed to decipher the<br>clues left behind by Lord Crwys and Lady Hefin, two<br>more of the clan elders. We should try to find them.
2025-09-12 13:46:15 [INFO] Continue
