2025-09-12 14:14:34 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:14:34 [INFO] Can continue: Lord Iorwerth
2025-09-12 14:14:34 [INFO] Can continue: Oh I will, one way or another. But in case it wasn't<br>clear, let me explain the situation.
2025-09-12 14:14:34 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:14:35 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:14:35 [INFO] Can continue: Lord Iorwerth
2025-09-12 14:14:35 [INFO] Can continue: As we speak, my forces are dealing with the last of<br>your rebels and rounding up your citizens. You have<br>no way to fight, and nowhere to run.
2025-09-12 14:14:35 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:14:36 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:14:36 [INFO] Can continue: Lord Iorwerth
2025-09-12 14:14:36 [INFO] Can continue: Of course, I could just have you all killed right now.<br>After the trouble you've all caused me, it wouldn't be an<br>unreasonable act. However, I am not without mercy,<br>and I will not draw blood unless I have to.
2025-09-12 14:14:36 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:14:38 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:14:38 [INFO] Can continue: Lord Iorwerth
2025-09-12 14:14:38 [INFO] Can continue: Instead, I give you a choice. Give me the orb, and I<br>will withdraw my forces, leaving you in peace. Refuse,<br>and the blood of those citizens will be on your hands.
2025-09-12 14:14:38 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:14:39 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:14:39 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 14:14:39 [INFO] Can continue: We do not barter with your kind!
