2025-09-12 14:19:04 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:04 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 14:19:04 [INFO] Can continue: Ysgawyn...
2025-09-12 14:19:04 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:05 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:05 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 14:19:05 [INFO] Can continue: He wasn't a friend, to any of us. Everything he cared<br>about he lost a long time ago.
2025-09-12 14:19:05 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:06 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:06 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 14:19:06 [INFO] Can continue: But he didn't give up. To the very end, he fought for a<br>cause he believed in, our cause.
2025-09-12 14:19:06 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:08 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:08 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 14:19:08 [INFO] Can continue: And now he's gone. Along with the orb and that traitor,<br>Arianwyn. Lord Iorwerth has everything he needs now.<br>He'll be preparing to move on the temple as we speak.
2025-09-12 14:19:08 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:09 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:09 [INFO] Can continue: Ilfeen
2025-09-12 14:19:09 [INFO] Can continue: We can't give up Islwyn. If we do, then he died for<br>nothing.
2025-09-12 14:19:09 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:11 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:11 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 14:19:11 [INFO] Can continue: Oh I don't intend to give up, but make no mistake, this<br>is a fight we're unlikely to win.
2025-09-12 14:19:11 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:12 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:12 [INFO] Can continue: Eluned
2025-09-12 14:19:12 [INFO] Can continue: So what do we do? Baxtorian?
2025-09-12 14:19:12 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:14 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:14 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:14 [INFO] Can continue: I... I don't think there's anything we can do. Lord<br>Iorwerth will destroy us if we try to stop him.
2025-09-12 14:19:14 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:14 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:14 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 14:19:14 [INFO] Can continue: Maybe, but we have to try. What else is there?
2025-09-12 14:19:14 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:15 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:15 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:15 [INFO] Can continue: We'd be throwing lives away...
2025-09-12 14:19:15 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:17 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:17 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 14:19:17 [INFO] Can continue: Well Lord Iorwerth seemed to think you were no<br>stranger to that. Why did he think that?
2025-09-12 14:19:17 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:18 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:18 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:18 [INFO] Can continue: I don't know, probably just some lie he tells himself.
2025-09-12 14:19:18 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:19 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:19 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 14:19:19 [INFO] Can continue: Hmm. I don't believe you.
2025-09-12 14:19:19 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:20 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:20 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:20 [INFO] Can continue: You'd trust Lord Iorwerth over me?
2025-09-12 14:19:20 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:20 [INFO] ANTIBAN: mouse_off_screen
2025-09-12 14:19:22 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:22 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 14:19:22 [INFO] Can continue: I wouldn't trust Lord Iorwerth if my life depended on<br>it. I know a liar when I see one though, and I can tell<br>you're not being honest about something.
2025-09-12 14:19:22 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:23 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:23 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 14:19:23 [INFO] Can continue: What happened? Tell us.
2025-09-12 14:19:23 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:24 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:24 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:24 [INFO] Can continue: I...
2025-09-12 14:19:24 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:26 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:26 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:26 [INFO] Can continue: It was after we were defeated by Lord Iorwerth. With<br>Prifddinas lost to us, we returned to our kingdom in<br>the east. We'd been gone for years by then, and in<br>our absence, the kingdom had fallen to our other foes.
2025-09-12 14:19:26 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:27 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:27 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:27 [INFO] Can continue: So many dead... my people, the ones I was meant to<br>protect. But that wasn't the worst of it. Glarial, my<br>beloved, she was taken from me.
2025-09-12 14:19:27 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:28 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:28 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:28 [INFO] Can continue: We searched far and wide, desperate to find her. At<br>times it felt like we were close, but the enemy always<br>managed to elude us.
2025-09-12 14:19:28 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:29 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:29 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:29 [INFO] Can continue: Eventually, we managed to track her captors to some<br>caves south of our ruined kingdom. It was clearly a<br>trap, but I was a fool. I was so blind in my desire to<br>find her, I didn't consider the obvious.
2025-09-12 14:19:29 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:30 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:30 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:30 [INFO] Can continue: I sent my soldiers in, the few that I still had. They<br>fought the best they could, but it was hopeless. They<br>were massacred.
2025-09-12 14:19:30 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:31 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:31 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:31 [INFO] Can continue: After that, I knew I couldn't carry on. I was alone and<br>powerless. So I sealed myself away, in the hope that one<br>day she would come back to me.
2025-09-12 14:19:31 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:32 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:32 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 14:19:32 [INFO] Can continue: You... you killed them? You killed them all?
2025-09-12 14:19:32 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:33 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:33 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:33 [INFO] Can continue: I did. But you don't understand, I loved my wife. If<br>there was a chance of freeing her, I had to take it.
2025-09-12 14:19:33 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:34 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:34 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 14:19:34 [INFO] Can continue: You think I don't understand love? I knew love, for<br>Eirlys! My mother! Your daughter! She died in your<br>war, while you hid away!
2025-09-12 14:19:34 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:35 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:35 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 14:19:35 [INFO] Can continue: Lord Iorwerth was right! You're just a coward!
2025-09-12 14:19:35 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:36 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:39 [INFO] Can continue: Eluned
2025-09-12 14:19:39 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn, where are you going?
2025-09-12 14:19:39 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:40 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:40 [INFO] Can continue: Islwyn
2025-09-12 14:19:40 [INFO] Can continue: The Underground Pass! I intend to fight for my<br>people, even if their own king won't!
2025-09-12 14:19:40 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:41 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:45 [INFO] LAG DETECTED 1404ms
2025-09-12 14:19:47 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:47 [INFO] Can continue: I used to think I was a good king, one that took care<br>of his people. Thanks to me, they had roofs over their<br>heads and food for their tables.
2025-09-12 14:19:47 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:47 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:47 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:47 [INFO] Can continue: And yet... I never loved them, not really. The only<br>thing I loved was her, my Glarial.
2025-09-12 14:19:47 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:48 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:48 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:48 [INFO] Can continue: When they took her from me... I was torn apart. I<br>vowed I would get her back no matter the cost. That<br>vow destroyed my people... I destroyed my people. In<br>the end... I became just like Lord Iorwerth.
2025-09-12 14:19:48 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:50 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:50 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:19:50 [INFO] Can continue: Maybe you did fail your people, you didn't destroy<br>them though.
2025-09-12 14:19:50 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:51 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:51 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:51 [INFO] Can continue: Maybe not then... but now...
2025-09-12 14:19:51 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:52 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:52 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:19:52 [INFO] Can continue: You think this is over? Is that it? Lord Iorwerth beats<br>us once so we just give up? If you truly think that<br>then yes, you have destroyed your people!
2025-09-12 14:19:52 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:53 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:53 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:19:53 [INFO] Can continue: Do you want to just rot here? Wallowing in your own<br>self pity while you lose the little you still have?
2025-09-12 14:19:53 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:54 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:54 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:54 [INFO] Can continue: What other option is there?
2025-09-12 14:19:54 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:55 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:55 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:19:55 [INFO] Can continue: We can fight! Lord Iorwerth doesn't win until he gets<br>into the Temple of Light! We can still stop this!
2025-09-12 14:19:55 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:56 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:56 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:56 [INFO] Can continue: But he outnumbers us ten to one... We'll all die.
2025-09-12 14:19:56 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:57 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:57 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:19:57 [INFO] Can continue: Surely it's better to die trying than to live a life of<br>regret? I'd have thought you'd know that better than<br>anyone.
2025-09-12 14:19:57 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:19:59 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:19:59 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:19:59 [INFO] Can continue: I... I can't...
2025-09-12 14:19:59 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:00 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:00 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:20:00 [INFO] Can continue: Oh for crying out loud! You have got to be the biggest<br>waste of space I have ever met! I've met goblins with<br>more of a spine than you! For once in your miserable<br>life why don't you actually do something worthwhile?
2025-09-12 14:20:00 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:02 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:02 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:20:02 [INFO] Can continue: You... You're awful at pep talks.
2025-09-12 14:20:02 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:03 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:03 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:20:03 [INFO] Can continue: It wasn't meant to be a pep talk!
2025-09-12 14:20:03 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:05 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:05 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:20:05 [INFO] Can continue: ...
2025-09-12 14:20:05 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:06 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:06 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:20:06 [INFO] Can continue: *sigh* Look... Ask yourself this... What would she want?
2025-09-12 14:20:06 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:07 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:07 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:20:07 [INFO] Can continue: She... She'd want me to save them.
2025-09-12 14:20:07 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:08 [INFO] LAG DETECTED 815ms
2025-09-12 14:20:09 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:09 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:20:09 [INFO] Can continue: Then why are we still stood around talking? We've got<br>work to do!
2025-09-12 14:20:09 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:09 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:09 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:20:09 [INFO] Can continue: I... You're right... We don't have a plan though.
2025-09-12 14:20:09 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:11 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:11 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:20:11 [INFO] Can continue: Lord Iorwerth only has one way into the Temple of<br>Light, the dwarf tunnel from the Underground Pass.<br>We need to stop him getting through.
2025-09-12 14:20:11 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:12 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:12 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:20:12 [INFO] Can continue: How?
2025-09-12 14:20:12 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:13 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:13 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:20:13 [INFO] Can continue: The dwarves should be able to seal the tunnel. We'll<br>need to defend them while they do.
2025-09-12 14:20:13 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:14 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:14 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:20:14 [INFO] Can continue: But we don't have the strength to withstand Lord<br>Iorwerth's forces.
2025-09-12 14:20:14 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:15 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:15 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:20:15 [INFO] Can continue: We have the clan elders, their combined power is an<br>army in itself.
2025-09-12 14:20:15 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:17 [INFO] LAG DETECTED 762ms
2025-09-12 14:20:17 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:17 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:20:17 [INFO] Can continue: Not all the clan elders. We're still missing two.
2025-09-12 14:20:17 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:18 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:18 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:20:18 [INFO] Can continue: Well have you deciphered their clues?
2025-09-12 14:20:18 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:19 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:19 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:20:19 [INFO] Can continue: I have, but there's a problem. We should hopefully be<br>able to find Lady Meilyr. But Lady Ithell, she died in<br>the early days of the war.
2025-09-12 14:20:19 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:20 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:20 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:20:20 [INFO] Can continue: That's not good. Did she have any descendants?
2025-09-12 14:20:20 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:22 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:22 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:20:22 [INFO] Can continue: I had a look. Kelyn Ithell is her closest living relative.<br>Problem is, we don't just need a Lady Ithell, we need<br>the Lady Ithell.
2025-09-12 14:20:22 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:23 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:23 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:20:23 [INFO] Can continue: Hmmm. How did she die?
2025-09-12 14:20:23 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:24 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:24 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:20:24 [INFO] Can continue: An illness of some sort, I never actually knew what it<br>was. She'd had it for years.
2025-09-12 14:20:24 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:26 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:26 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:20:26 [INFO] Can continue: For years? So she'd have been ill when she gave you<br>her clue. If she knew she was dying, maybe her clue<br>reflects that.
2025-09-12 14:20:26 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:27 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:27 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:20:27 [INFO] Can continue: What do you mean?
2025-09-12 14:20:27 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:28 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:28 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:20:28 [INFO] Can continue: Knowledge can be passed on. Maybe the clue will lead<br>us to her knowledge.
2025-09-12 14:20:28 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:29 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:29 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:20:29 [INFO] Can continue: I... I suppose you could be right.
2025-09-12 14:20:29 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:30 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:30 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:20:30 [INFO] Can continue: It's worth a shot at least. Leave it with me and I'll see<br>what I can do. In the meantime, you should take the<br>others to the dwarf camp in the Underground Pass.
2025-09-12 14:20:30 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:32 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:32 [INFO] Can continue: PLAYER_NAME
2025-09-12 14:20:32 [INFO] Can continue: See if you can get in contact with General Hining and<br>the new King of Ardougne as well. Maybe they'll be<br>willing to help us.
2025-09-12 14:20:32 [INFO] Continue
2025-09-12 14:20:33 [INFO] Solving dialogue
2025-09-12 14:20:33 [INFO] Can continue: Baxtorian
2025-09-12 14:20:33 [INFO] Can continue: I'll see what I can do. We'll need to work quickly<br>though, Lord Iorwerth will be preparing his forces as we<br>speak. Now I guess you'll be wanting to hear those<br>clues?
